Ask HN: Do any language communities post bug-fixed GPT transcripts?
text:
(After bugfixing GPT's Nim help for an hour...)

I wondered if any language communities have taken to posting bug-fixed LLM transcripts?

Programmers often fix posted code in Discord all day anyway. The Nim discord was amazing for this last I tried it.

So it seems like, potentially, hooking the fixes to a search engine could be really helpful, even if N-1 generation tech...?

Or perhaps it could even be worth integrating with a code documentation system.

Anyway, love to hear if there's anything like this no matter the language.

Looking for advice for my new AI-powered side project
text:
Hello everyone,

Recently I started working on my new AI-powered chrome extension.

It basically helps you to simplify your workflow and save time. You can select a specific text from a website and get its definition, make content based on that, rephrase it, or even make tweets based on the selected text from the website to share on your wall.

Also, it supports command base work on the text field of a website. You can easily create content, generate tweets, write code, write mail, rephrase the content, translate content for your customer support, generate more detailed mid-journey prompts, and more without switching the tab.

It is an extension that will work on any website.

It is still under development and I am almost done. I shared a pre-order offer for early adapters 2 days ago. But no sale yet. So, Should I continue the work or not?

Check - https://vitruo.simplef.net/

All advice and feedbacks are welcome.
